Validated Multi-Perspectives Visual Features in Imagery with Interpretable Machine Learning for Detecting Rural Vacant Courtyards in North China

2025-01-12

1.load packages

library(xgboost)
library(shapviz)
library(ggplot2)
library(readxl)
library(tidyverse)
library(Matrix)

2.read data

2.1 divide dataset, trainset(700) and testset(299).

dt <- read_excel("features.examples.xlsx")
str(dt)
#> tibble [999 × 11] (S3: tbl_df/tbl/data.frame)
#>  $ Type                                    : num [1:999] 1 0 0 0 0 0 1 1 0 0 ...
#>  $ Main building door and window management: num [1:999] 3 3 3 2 1 3 3 3 3 3 ...
#>  $ Solar water heaters                     : num [1:999] 0 1 1 0 0 1 0 0 0 1 ...
#>  $ Courtyard plants management             : num [1:999] 1 2 2 3 1 2 2 0 0 2 ...
#>  $ Residence entrance management           : num [1:999] 1 1 2 1 0 2 0 2 1 2 ...
#>  $ Residence enceinte wall edge management : num [1:999] 2 3 2 2 3 2 0 0 0 1 ...
#>  $ Main building structure                 : num [1:999] 1 1 1 1 0 1 0 3 1 1 ...
#>  $ Main building roof                      : num [1:999] 2 2 2 2 3 2 2 1 1 2 ...
#>  $ Homestead exterior wall management      : num [1:999] 2 3 3 3 2 3 1 3 3 3 ...
#>  $ Front road width                        : num [1:999] 0 0 1 1 0 1 0 0 1 2 ...
#>  $ Front road type                         : num [1:999] 2 2 2 2 2 0 0 2 0 2 ...
dt <- as.data.frame(dt)
dt[,2:11] <- lapply(dt[,2:11], factor)

set.seed(0)  
s = sample(999,700)  
trainset = dt[s,]  
testset = dt[-s,]

trainset.Y <- trainset[,1]
trainset.overhead <- trainset[,2:6]
trainset.horizontal <- trainset[,7:11]
trainset.final <- trainset[,c(2,3:5)]

testset.Y <- testset[,1]
testset.overhead <- testset[,2:6]
testset.horizontal <- testset[,7:11]
testset.final <- testset[,c(2,3:5)]

3 overhead perspective model

dtrain.overhead <- xgb.DMatrix(data.matrix(trainset.overhead), 
                               label=trainset.Y)
dtest.overhead <- xgb.DMatrix(data.matrix(testset.overhead), 
                               label=testset.Y)

fit.overhead <- xgb.train(
  params = list(learning_rate = 0.1, objective = "binary:logistic"),
  data = dtrain.overhead,
  nrounds = 65L)

pre_xgb = round(predict(fit.overhead,newdata = dtest.overhead))  
(test.overhead <- table(testset.Y,pre_xgb,dnn=c("true","pre")))
#>     pre
#> true   0   1
#>    0 182  22
#>    1  28  67
(Accuracy.test.overhead = sum(diag(test.overhead))/nrow(testset.overhead))
#> [1] 0.8327759
(Recall.test.overhead = test.overhead[1,1]/(test.overhead[1,1]+
                                              test.overhead[1,2]))
#> [1] 0.8921569
(Precision.test.overhead = test.overhead[1,1]/(test.overhead[1,1]+
                                                 test.overhead[2,1]))
#> [1] 0.8666667
(F1 <- 2*Precision.test.overhead*Recall.test.overhead/(Precision.test.overhead+
                                                         Recall.test.overhead))
#> [1] 0.8792271
shp <- shapviz(fit.overhead, 
               X_pred = data.matrix(testset.overhead),
               X = testset.overhead)

sv_importance(shp,show_numbers = TRUE)+
  theme_bw()

sv_importance(shp, kind = "beeswarm")+
  theme_bw()

dtrain.horizontal <- xgb.DMatrix(data.matrix(trainset.horizontal),
